<plot>Two female Londoners set out on a 21 day journey around the world. Their first destination is a cable car ride in Hong Kong Disneyland. Their visit to Australia puts them in contact with a lonely traveler by the name of Becky Benson, but by far the most significant place that they travel to is their final destination of South Africa. Here, they make a spiritual connection in the land of their ancestors. It is a homecoming in the bicentenary year of the abolition of the slave trade, and it wraps up their 21 day journey around the world.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?045938</url></doc>
